<DOC><DOCNO> AP880311-0301 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-11-88 1446EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-TheWeekAhead     03-11 0348</FIRST><SECOND>BC-The Week Ahead,0377</SECOND><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Here are the major business events and economic events scheduledfor the coming week (some dates are tentative):</TEXT><BYLINE>MONDAY, March 14</BYLINE><TEXT>      CLEVELAND _ A federal judge has scheduled a hearing to reviewthe constitutionality of Ohio's anti-takeover law, filed by theItalian tiremaker Pirelli in an attempt to prevent Firestone Tire andamp;Rubber Co. from using the law to thwart Pirelli's $1.86 billionbuyout bid.   WASHINGTON _ Business inventories for January will be releasedat 10 a.m. by the Commerce Department.</TEXT><BYLINE>TUESDAY, March 15</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The current account report covering trade inmerchandise and services, for fourth quarter 1987, will be releasedat 10 a.m. by the Commerce Department.   DETROIT _ The nation's automakers will release auto sales forfirst 10 days of March.   LONDON _ Chancellor of the Exchequer Nigel Lawson presents theBritish budget to Parliament.</TEXT><BYLINE>WEDNESDAY, March 16</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ Housing starts for February will be released at8:30 a.m. by the Commerce Department; industrial production forFebruary will be released at 9:15 a.m. by the Federal Reserve.   WASHINGTON _ The House Labor Committee has scheduled a finalvote on legislation increasing the federal minimum wage to $5.05 anhour over next four years.   RICHMOND _ A bankrupcty hearing is scheduled to review latestversion of A.H. Robins Co. reorganization plan.</TEXT><BYLINE>THURSDAY, March 17</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ Merchandise trade for January will be released at8:30 a.m. by the Commerce Department; factory use for February,release time uncertain, by the Federal Reserve.   JABALPUR, India _ The High Court is scheduled to rule on UnionCarbide's appeal of interim relief order to Bhopal victims.</TEXT><BYLINE>FRIDAY, March 18</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ President Reagan's Commission of Privatization isscheduled to issue its recommendations.   MEXICO CITY _ Mexico marks the 50th anniversary of thenationalization of the oil industry.   CONSTANCE, West Germany _ U.S. Trade Representative ClaytonYeutter and trade ministers of West Germany, France, Britain andSpain meet to discuss the Airbus and European subsidies to Airbus.</TEXT><HEAD>The AP</HEAD></DOC>